n: Pan de Elote Facil (Easy Corn Bread)
des: "An easy Mexican cake made with fresh sweet corn kernels and store-bought pancake mix. It's sweet - Mexicans enjoy it as a dessert with warm honey on top."
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Combine corn, milk, butter, sugar, and eggs in a blender; blend until smooth. Pour mixture into a bowl; stir in pancake mix until batter is well blended. Pour batter into the prepared baking dish.
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
